<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="587">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33904" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole obtusospinosa Pergande" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole obtusospinosa Pergande" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obtusospinosa">Pheidole obtusospinosa Pergande</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageNumber="587">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33904" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole obtusospinosa Pergande" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole obtusospinosa Pergande" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obtusospinosa">Pheidole obtusospinosa Pergande</taxonomicName>
1896: 889. Junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:142461" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole subdentata Pergande" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole subdentata Pergande" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subdentata">Pheidole subdentata Pergande</taxonomicName>
1896: 888, synonymy by Wheeler, 1914c: 50; 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:142461" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole subdentata Pergande" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole subdentata Pergande" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subdentata">subdentata Pergande</taxonomicName>
is ajunior secondary homonym of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:142485" genus="Oecophthora" lsidName="Oecophthora subdentata Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Oecophthora subdentata Mayr" pageNumber="587" rank="species" species="subdentata">Oecophthora subdentata Mayr</taxonomicName>
1853b: 145, later transferred to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:24885" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole Westwood" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole Westwood" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pheidole</taxonomicName>
and a synonym of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33916" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole pallidula (Nylander)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole pallidula (Nylander)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidula">P. pallidula (Nylander)</taxonomicName>
of Eurasia; hence 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33903" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole obtusopilosa Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole obtusopilosa Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obtusopilosa">obtusopilosa</taxonomicName>
is first available name. Syn.: 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:142614" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole arizonica Santschi" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole arizonica Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arizonica">Pheidole arizonica Santschi</taxonomicName>
191 ld: 3, synonymy by Creighton 1958: 211.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="587">Types Nat. Mus. Nat. Hist. U. S.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="587">
Etymology L 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33904" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole obtusospinosa Pergande" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole obtusospinosa Pergande" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obtusospinosa">obtusospinosa</taxonomicName>
, with blunt thorns, referring to the propodeal spines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="587">
Diagnosis A large trimorphic species placed in the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33930" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole pilifera (Roger)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole pilifera (Roger)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilifera">pilifera</taxonomicName>
group because of the 2-toothed hypostoma of the major but with other traits conforming to the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33735" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole fallax Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole fallax Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fallax">fallax</taxonomicName>
group. Very close to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33783" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole hirtula Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole hirtula Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtula">hirtula</taxonomicName>
, distinguished most readily in the supermajor, as illustrated, by the elongate foveae of the rear half of the dorsum of the head, with the interspaces densely foveolate and opaque. The tangled taxonomic history of this species and the true status of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34085" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole vaslitii Pergande" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole vaslitii Pergande" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vaslitii">vaslitii</taxonomicName>
, previously associated with it but now revealed as a junior synonym or sibling species ofhyatti (q.v.), have been presented by Ward (2000).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="587">Measurements (mm) Supermajor: HW 2.50, HL 2.36, SL 1.12, EL 0.26, PW 1.06.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="587">Major: HW 1.44, HL 1.46, SL 1.12, EL 0.24, PW 0.72.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="587">Minor: HW 0.62, HL 0.80, SL 0.98, EL 0.16, PW 0.44.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="587">Color All castes: yellowish to reddish brown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="587">Range Known from the mountains of southern Arizona at 300-1900 m, and from Nayarit to Nuevo Leon in Mexico.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="587">
biology Stefan Cover (unpublished field notes), who has collected 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33904" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole obtusospinosa Pergande" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole obtusospinosa Pergande" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obtusospinosa">obtusospinosa</taxonomicName>
many times in southern Arizona, has found it consistently in woodland, variously composed of different combinations of pine, oak, and juniper. It typically nests under rocks, although Cover found one colony beneath a cow pat and another 2.5 m from the ground in the dead branch of a standing oak tree (
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:142614" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole arizonica Santschi" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole arizonica Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arizonica">Quercus arizonica</taxonomicName>
). Creighton (1958) reports that colonies are much smaller than those of the closely related 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33783" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole hirtula Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole hirtula Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtula">hirtula</taxonomicName>
, and that in southern Arizona nuptial flights occur in early July.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
